East African marketing firm, Aggrey &amp; Clifford has been honoured as among the best agencies. The firm, which is headquartered in Dar es Salaam, but with operations in Nairobi, Kampala and Kigali, was recognised as one of the top independent advertising agencies in the world. This is due to its creative and thought leadership work in the marketing communications industry. Aggrey &amp; Clifford CEO, Rashid Tenga said, &quot;We are grateful to our clients who have always believed in our creativity and ability to build brands.&quot; The thenetworkone and Campaign magazine, London ranked the agency among 12 other advertising agencies where The Jupiter Drawing Room and King James both from South Africa were the only other agencies to be included in the ranking from Africa.